Package: baker
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Analysis Kit for Etiology Research
Version: 0.1
Date: 2015-07-29
Authors@R: as.person(c(
    "Zhenke Wu <zhwu@jhu.edu> [aut, cre]",
    "Wei Fu <wfu@jhu.edu> [ctb]",
    "Scott Zeger <sz@jhu.edu> [aut]"
    ))
Description: Nested Partially-Latent Class Models (npLCM) for Inference of
    Population Disease Etiology and Individual Diagnosis. In the motivating 
    scientific study, Penumonia Etiology Research for Child Health, the scientists
    usually call them "population etiology pie" and "individual etiology pie" for 
    their compositional nature, hence the name of the package.
Depends: 
    R(>= 3.1)
Imports: 
    R2WinBUGS(>= 2.1),
    lubridate(>= 1.3),
    binom(>= 1.1),
    coda(>= 0.16),
    ks(>= 1.9),
    robCompositions(>= 1.9),
    ggplot2(>= 1.0),
    gridExtra(>= 2.0),
    reshape2(>= 1.4),
    splines
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    testthat,
    bibtex,
    knitcitations
VignetteBuilder: knitr
